Police officers have been urged to behave ethically in their duties to win public confidence.Athi River police chief Peter Kiema said a combination of work ethic and National Police Service functions have earned him and the police station Ipoa awards twice.&ldquo;When you join the two, you will render the best services to wananchi,&rdquo; Kiema said in his office yesterday.He said the public needs to be served in police stations with dignity and without discrimination. &ldquo;Ensure all enjoy their constitutional rights,&rdquo; he said.Kiema condemned officers who conduct malicious prosecutions of innocent citizens.He said the station relates well with the public through public barazas, groups and stakeholders&rsquo; meetings through community policing.